text: Lewis County Courthouse in Hohenwald, Tennessee is a historic courthouse building built in 1939 that is listed on the National Register of Historic Places. It was deemed significant as "an excellent local example of Public Works Administration (PWA) Modern architecture". It was funded by the Public Works Administration, was designed by Nashville architects Hart & Russell, and was built by Nashville contractor Chrichlow & Yearwood. It is a red brick building. It has three original jail cells on its third floor. with (see photo captions pages 14-15 of text document) ==References== Category:Art Deco architecture in Tennessee Category:Buildings and structures in Lewis County, Tennessee Category:Courthouses on the National Register of Historic Places in Tennessee Category:County courthouses in Tennessee Category:National Register of Historic Places in Lewis County, Tennessee
